article.headline: Butler 31, Morehead St. 21
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Matt Kobli passed for two fourth-quarter touchdowns and Butler returned a punt and an interception for two other second-half scores as the Bulldogs came from behind to beat Morehead State 31-21 Saturday. Butler (6-1, 4-0 Pioneer) trailed Morehead (3-5, 1-3) 21-3 at halftime but scored 28 unanswered points beginning with Jacob Fritz's returned an interception of an Evan Sawyer pass 39 yards for a touchdown early in the third period. The Bulldogs added three more touchdowns over a span of 7:34. Tadd Dombart returned a punt 75 yards with a second remaining in the third quarter, then Kobli threw touchdown passes covering 13 yards to Dan Bohrer and 19 yards to Eddie McHale. Kobli completed 25-of-40 passes to eight different receivers for 259 yards. Zach Watkins pulled in four passes for 75 yards to lead Butler receivers. Morehead grabbed a 14-0 first quarter lead on touchdown runs of 6 yards by Cory Jackson and 37 yards by Nick Feldman. Feldman later collected a Sawyer pass for an 83-yard touchdown with 3:46 left before halftime to build the 21-3 lead after Butler's Jordan Quiroz kicked a 36-yard field goal. Eleven Morehead runners rushed 44 times for a total of 194 yards. Feldman had three receptions for 140 yards. Butler had four sacks for 42 yards lost. Grant Hunter had two of the sacks.
